<p>How to modify type slice inside method? I tried  <a href="http://play.golang.org/p/ul2n8mk6ye" rel="nofollow">http://play.golang.org/p/ul2n8mk6ye</a></p>  <pre><code>type Test []string  func (test Test) Add(str string) {     test = append(test, str) }  func main() {     test := Test{}     test.Add("value")     fmt.Println(len(test))//0 } </code></pre>  <p>And <a href="http://play.golang.org/p/nV9IO7E5sp" rel="nofollow">http://play.golang.org/p/nV9IO7E5sp</a></p>  <pre><code>type Test []string  func (test *Test) Add(str string) {     v := append(*test, str)     test = &amp;v }  func main() {         test := Test{}     test.Add("value")     fmt.Println(len(test))//0 } </code></pre>  <p>But it does not work.</p>